# TypeScript Conventions

## Language and typing

- Use strict TypeScript (`strict: true`) and avoid `any`; use `unknown` + narrowing.
- Export explicit types for data contracts from a dedicated module (e.g. `src/types/lore.ts`).
- Prefer readonly data shapes for normalized content where possible.

## Runtime validation

- Validate external/raw data using schema validators (recommended: Zod).
- Parse at boundaries; avoid carrying unvalidated external payloads into UI.

## App boundaries

- Separate `content` (authoritative data), `compute` (derived stats), and `ui` layers.
- Keep transform utilities pure and side-effect free.

## Error handling

- Throw typed errors in scripts and return user-safe fallbacks in UI.
- Include actionable context in errors (`characterId`, `version`, `source`).
